subsection.def:
Board
                    (委員會) means the Pneumoconiosis Compensation
                Fund Board established under section 25;

compensation
                    (補償) means compensation as provided by this
                Ordinance;

employment
                    (僱用) includes any self-employment in any
                trade, business or profession;

Fund
                    (基金) means the Pneumoconiosis Compensation
                Fund established by section 27;

paragraph.content:
a cohabitee, that is to say, any person who at the date of death of a
                        person was living with that person as that person’s wife or husband;
                        and

fibrosis of the lungs due to dust of asbestos or dust containing
                        asbestos, whether or not such disease is accompanied by tuberculosis of the
                        lungs, or any other disease caused by exposure to such dust;

in relation to any construction operations, means the value of the
                        construction operations as determined under section 39C;
                        and

if the contract is a term contract under which works orders are issued,
                        the aggregate of the values of all construction operations carried out as
                        required by those works orders;

to any person who, since the commencement of the amending Ordinance, has
                    commenced an appeal under section 20 from a decision of the Board
                    made under this Ordinance prior to its amendment;

to any person who has at any time received damages for death or disability
                    resulting from pneumoconiosis within the meaning of section 13;
                    or
